I think we have some good talking points for Alabamians. We know that Trump is not good for Alabama: for one, this trade war with China lowered the prices of our biggest crops (particularly cotton). He also not only didn’t do anything to help with our infrastructure, he actually deprioritized it.
If Trump does what he’s planning with Project 2025, it will literally put our lives in danger, making us more vulnerable to natural disasters and without any early warning systems.

What permission do I need, in carrying out discussions on this channel #alpolitics, to include links to https://al4bidenharrisjones.blogspot.com/2024/07/purpose.html? Thank you.

It depends on what you mean by permission and by carrying out.  Individually we can engage in whatever political conversations we choose to.   The rub comes when it relates to these other activities being linked to the official campaign.  That’s what we want to avoid.  


Even if the mission of these other initiatives are essential and the talking points are solid; the campaign cannot take on liability for it.

To that end, references and discussions of external platforms like that can only reside at https://discord.com/channels/1242249109298221066/1268426751164551199 within this server so that there is a clear delineation.

I hope that helped answer your question, please let me know if it missed the mark.

So... I had an interesting convo with Barry Moore. (Republican Congressman, District 1) Essentially, he told me he doesn't think abortion is healthcare, that people are being "killed by woke", and that kids are being pumped full of hormones that are giving them mental illnesses and destroying their bones (which he say, cannot be reversed. I'm assuming he's talking about gender affirming care. Also, this is not true. Some of it is fully reversible as I am aware. I'm no expert though and still researching for my video I'm making). He also told me that abortion clinics don't provide any other services (Which by that, I guess he's meaning Planned Parenthood?)

Just passing this along, since we've been talking about Alabama issues and he probably represents what people in the other camp really believe. I'm already making a video about this dude, and putting this convo with it. (Yes I have receipts, it was an email)

Hey would anyone be interested in joining a debate watch party in Huntsville - like in District 5?

Many people think its all the hormones in our food actually. That is actually true which is why I'm starting to watch my food.  What they don't get is that GMO isn't hormones it is a method to modify the actual food so that it has properties considered "good" for the product. That is a definite mixed bag of what is good and not good.  For example, our bananas are GMO - there is only ONE type of banana. Is that good - not really but it isn't bad for you to eat them. The reason it is bad is that if that variety ever developed something that killed them - it would kill them all.
So - noone in my family would be interested in a watch party - but I would love to have one with anyone from the Huntsville area. Anyone interested in either hosting or attending one?

**Strict Fundraising Rules (it’s the law):**
We can only fundraise on behalf of: Democratic National Committee, Harris Victory Fund or Harris for President directly. 
We can recruit for "non-official events" that are hosted by partner organizations or volunteers in ⁠non-official-events-only. We can recruit into anything that is listed on events.democrats.org or a state democratic party's mobilize.
Rule 3 Note > Relevance: Do not post links to petitions or other calls to action that haven’t been approved by Staff. This forum is not intended for debates. Additionally, do not attempt to raise funds or share fundraising links for any entity besides the Democratic National Committee. Using this server to raise funds for yourself, another candidate, or another organization violates campaign finance law and is strictly prohibited. Anyone who violates the rules is subject to removal or time out.
When in doubt, ask @Community Moderator.

Are there any Alabamians here with high school seniors (or other high school students) in their lives? The Civics Center is offering a $150 gift card to students who hold a voter registration drive at their school (up to 3 per school).
